text:
Avery Remfert  Hololive is a company/label that a lot of vtubers are part of. Think something like Yung Money if you know about rap or WWE if you know about wrestling. Hololive will add new vtubers in a generational format, every few months or so about 5 new members will join the fray, they hold auditions and only the best of the best are accepted in. Sometimes they'll also scout for some really talented people and request that they join. It's a Japanese company that has mostly Japanese girls but they do have a really popular English branch called Hololive EN. Gura is one of the five members of the first generation of Hololive EN called HoloMyth, with the basic theme being that they're all mythical entities that have YouTube channels (the grim reaper, a phoenix, a shark from Atlantis [Gura], a time Traveller, and an eldritch entity)
Ina is another girl who is part of those original 5 EN members, she's the eldritch entity. Baelz Hakos is a member of the second generation of Hololive EN called HoloCouncil, with the theme being that they're all different aspects of reality... who have YouTube channels. Hakos Baelz is the avatar of chaos, and yes, HololiveEN has some really weird themes and designs... Hololive JP has pirates, elves, and rabbits, Hololive EN has the avatar of time...
There's a lot more to it than that but yeah Hololive is very cool, and you'll definitely enjoy your time in this community, the vtubers are funny and likable and the community is very wholesome.
